This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on relation extraction, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed architecture uses neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of recurrent and recursive neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its models on four datasets and discusses precision and recall, which are common evaluation metrics in information retrieval (cs.IR).
